title: Magritte (Great Modern Masters - Art Ebook).pdf
description:
Pdf / English / 1996 / 72 pag / 11 MB

Rene Magritte (1898-1967) created images that are among the most enigmatic in
modern art. His meticulously painted cloud-filled skies, bowler-hatted men, and
oversized household objects have had a profound influence on the art of the twentieth century. This is not a pipe, he wrote beneath his precisely realistic painting of a pipe, proposing the simple notion that a representation of a pipe and a pipe itself are not one and the same.
This book provides the reader with an introduction to the world of Magritte's magic realism, reproducing in color 63 of his most important works.
